patterns.pattern: / ACC: prefix format (common in medical billing)
/ Pattern 1: Explicit age statements (e.g., "92 years old", "age 95")
/ Pattern 2: Age with context labels (e.g., "Age: 91", "Patient age: 94")
/ Pattern for "X years old", "X year old", "X y/
/ Pattern 2: Explicit descriptor phrases (tattoo, scar, birthmark)
/ Pattern 5: Biometric ID codes (IRIS-123456, DNA-ABC123, FP-987654, etc.)
/ Standalone card numbers (13-19 digits with optional separators)
/ Pattern 2: Standalone DEA format (strict - valid first letters only)
/ Pattern 5: Medical device manufacturer prefixes (ABBOTT-, STRYKER-, BOSTON SCIENTIFIC, etc.)
/ Pattern 6: Common device serial prefixes (BS-, TAN-, etc.)
/ Validate it's actually a fax number (must contain "fax")
/ Must be 10 digits (US) or 11 digits (with country code 1)
/ Filter 0: Exact match false positive list (document structure phrases)
/ Filter 5: Ends with trailing words (captured too much)
/ Pattern 0: Last, First format (medical records format)
/ Pattern 0.5: Titled names (Dr. Smith, Mr. Jones)
/ Pattern 2: Standalone VINs (17 characters, strict validation)
/ ZIP+4 format (must check first to avoid partial match)
/ Apply patterns in order (ZIP+4 first to avoid partial matches)
